entry.title: [Privacy Sandbox] Add sentinel file to prevent crash looping for
entry.content:
attestations component.



A sentinel file is created in the attestations installation directory

just before the call to parse the attestations list. If there is any

crash or failure in parsing, the sentinel file is kept. Any subsequent

attempts to parse the attestations file will be denied. This prevents

crash looping.



If the parsing is successful, the sentinel file is removed immediately

after parsing is done.



For example, if the installation directory is

/user/chromium/PrivacySandboxAttestationsPreloaded/2023.8.18.0



The sentinel file is created at

/user/chromium/PrivacySandboxAttestationsPreloaded/2023.8.18.0/

attestations_sentinel



The sentinel file has empty content.



The sentinel file is removed when there is a new version downloaded by

the component updater. The sentinel file will be removed together with

the old version.

entry.title: [ios] Request expiration date as for expired cards in CVC prompt
entry.content:
This patch fixes a bug in the Card Verification Code prompt for

autofill. When the user wants to autofill a credit card already saved

in their profile, the CVC prompt is displayed. If the card is already

expired, they need to enter the new CVC and expiration date through

the prompt. The bug was about not requesting the expiration date right

away, so users would enter a CVC, the verification would fail and then

the expiration date would be required. The patch checks for expired

cards when the CVC prompt is presented and requires expiration date

accordingly. A unit test verifies the state of the prompt for expired

cards.



A minor refactoring was also needed to focus on the right field( expiration date or cvc ) after each UI transition.

entry.title: [ios] Fix the crash of NTPCoordinator.started
entry.content:
This CL removes DCHECK from -snapshotGenerator: because

`_NTPCoordinator.started` can be false when a page is loaded and then

immediately (=less than 1 second) a user tries to close an app.



1. A user opens a new tab page.

2. NewTabPageTabHelper::PageLoaded() is called and `NTPHelper->

IsActive()` becomes true. SnapshotTabHelper::PageLoaded() is called as

well and it posts a task to call SnapshotTabHelper::UpdateSnapshotWithCallback() with a 1-second delay.

3. A user tries to close an app before the delayed task

(UpdateSnapshotWithCallback()) is called.

4. The delayed task is called and then the crash occurs because `_NTPCoordinator.started` is NO.



In this case, we fall back to using the WebState's view.



Bug: 1478507

entry.title: [UNO] Choose bookmark model used for sync in ShoppingService
entry.content:
ShoppingService should select the appropriate bookmark model to use

based on the UNO opt-in status:

* If the user has sync-the-feature on - LocalOrSyncable bookmark model

should be used. This corresponds to the legacy state.

* If the user doesn't have sync-the-feature on, but is opted into

syncing bookmarks while being signed in - Account bookmark model

should be used instead.



In the long run, syncing from LocalOrSyncable model will be disabled.

When that happens - ShoppingService can be simplified to always use

Account bookmark model.



This CL revises how different parts of ShoppingService obtain

BookmarkModel instance and introduces

ShoppingService::GetBookmarkModelUsedForSync that returns the

appropriate model based on the logic explained above.

entry.title: [iOS] Migrate usage of ConsentLevel::kSync in omnibox autocomplete
entry.content:
Background: ConsentLevel::kSync is going away, and all users need

to be migrated to something else - see crbug.com/1447010.



Before this CL, AutocompleteProviderClientImpl::IsAuthenticated()

checked for ConsentLevel::kSync, which seemed wrong (independent of

the removal of kSync): This method is meant to return whether

there's a signed-in user, not whether they have Sync enabled (per

the comment in autocomplete_provider_client.h, and also judging

from its call sites).

So this CL updates it to use ConsentLevel::kSignin instead (behind

a killswitch, just in case).



Note that this is also more similar to the implementation on other

platforms, which checks for any accounts in the cookie jar (i.e. is

also independent of Sync).



Bug: 1462286, 1483272

entry.title: [BREFs]: Support non-origin-trial browser controlled feature
entry.content:
This CL implement WebIDL bindings generator to generate the correct

bindings for RFS features that aren't a origin trial.



1. WebIDL generator is_context_dependent now covers is_origin_trial and

is_browser_controlled

2. WebIDL generator explicitly checks is_origin_trial when generating

feature enablement statements for origin trial features (instead of

assuming context dependent runtime features are all origin trials)

3. Scope RFS template to only generates Set*Feature(token) in

RuntimeStateOverrideContext for origin trial features



Manually verified the generated files diff is what we expect:



* RFS no longer emits SetTestFeature(token) for TestFeature, which

is a non-origin-trial, browser controlled runtime feature

* WebIDL database pickle now includes Exposure.origin_trial_features

* No other delta



Bug: 1377000, b/294479032

entry.title: [Files app] Ducks: Add Selectors to the store
entry.content:
Introduces the concept of Selectors to the store.



Selectors are essentially functions that allow for a parts of the

store's state to be combined to create a value that can be read

at any moment in time, subscribed to for changes, or used directly

in lit components in way that allows them to automatically

re-render when selectors update.



Selectors can be combined to create new selectors and are

implemented efficiently through a DAG.



Selectors only emit new values when the fail the shallow

equality check with their previous state, freeing components

and other subscribers from the potentially tedius and repetitive

job of checking for equality when raw store updates are received.



Additionally, the SelectorEmitter class ensures that even if

multiple parents of a given selector emit, their common child

selector only emits once, instead of once for every parent that

has changes. It also guarantees that a selector's new value is

only ever calculated when at least one of its parents emits a

new value.



This CL adds unit tests in order to showcase how selectors can

be used in Files app.



Bug: b:297808212

Test: browser_tests FileManagerJsTest.Selector

entry.title: [Windows] Do not include string terminator in GetWindowText
entry.content:
WindowEnumerator::GetWindowText was including the trailing string

terminator in the body of the returned string. This CL fixes that as

well as makes several other changes:



- WindowEnumeratorTest.EnumerateTopLevelWindows had the same bug in its

independent implementation of GetWindowText. It is also fixed.

- WindowEnumerator has been whittled down to a single function, so

there's no need for a class anymore. It's now simply

base::win::EnumerateChildWindows, which is a little easier to use.

- base/win/window_enumerator.h no longer includes windows.h.

- GetWindowText has been renamed to GetWindowTextString so that it

doesn't accidentally get renamed to GetWindowTextW by windows.h.

- GetWindowTextString also handles the case where the actual text is

fewer characters than reported by GetWindowTextLength. MSDN explains a

few cases where this could happen.



Bug: 1482637

entry.title: dlp: Fix DCHECK crash when a warning times out
entry.content:
When a DLP warning times out we call the IOTaskController to complete

that task with an error. While we set the state correctly, completing

the task moves its progress_ to the complete_callback, which means that

processing the status update with that state can fail, specifically

when converting origin URLs which are now empty causing a DCHECK inside

storage_key.cc to fail.



However, after the task completes, it again sends the update to all the

observers and is removed from the IOTaskController::OnIOTaskComplete()

again. This only applies to CopyOrMoveIOTask-s, so to fix the issue,

CompleteWithError() now behaves similar to Cancel() - it only sets the

correct ProgressStatus with the error state and policy error details.

IOTaskController afterwards notifies the observers with the new status,

and removes the task which then deletes it and stops any in-flight

operations.

entry.title: Implement counters functionality for StyleContainmentScopeTree
entry.content:
As part of the css counters rework, the idea is to move contain: style

logic from counters to scope tree. This CL prepares the functionality

of the tree to be able to handle counters in correct way. For this,

CountersScope and CountersScopeTree are introduced that manage counters

inside one `contain: style` scope, represented by StyleContainmentScope.

The next step is to remove old logic from counters and connect them to the tree.



Design doc:

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1lc7OouWnelduHuRBxsQ9rmSS85q7E-h42NrOpKVkkoU
